                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.27919/2605.27919v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Illustration of FGO. (Top) During the forward diffusion process, full-frequency action trajectories are processed through a bank of low-pass filters, mapping them onto corresponding sub-frequency manifolds. The model is subsequently trained on noise-perturbed variants of these frequency-truncated actions. (Bottom) During the reverse denoising process, the guidance mechanism synthesizes composite vector fields that progressively drives the noisy samples away from the low-frequency foundation and toward the target full-frequency data manifold.",
                "position": 336
            }
        ]
